<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc3296da9-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s1978"><num value="1978">§ 1978.</num><heading> Reinstatement</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Reinstatement of insurance coverage granted under this subchapter but lapsed for nonpayment of premiums shall be under terms and conditions prescribed by the Secretary.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc3296daa-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/93/289/s9/a">Pub. L. 93–289, § 9(a)</ref>, <date date="1974-05-24">May 24, 1974</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/172">88 Stat. 172</ref>, § 778; renumbered § 1978 and amended <ref href="/us/pl/102/83">Pub. L. 102–83</ref>, §§ 4(b)(1), (2)(E), 5(a), <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/404-406">105 Stat. 404–406</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc3296dab-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc3296dac-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idc3296dad-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1991—<ref href="/us/pl/102/83">Pub. L. 102–83</ref> renumbered <ref href="/us/usc/t38/s778">section 778 of this title</ref> as this section and substituted “Secretary” for “Administrator”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idc3296dae-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idc3296daf-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective first day of third calendar month following May 1974, see <ref href="/us/pl/93/289/s12/4">section 12(4) of Pub. L. 93–289</ref>, set out as an Effective Date of 1974 Amendment note under <ref href="/us/usc/t38/s1968">section 1968 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
